Tracey Armah, better known by her alias Tracey Barbie, live streamed herself at this restaurant (without a mask) and was told to put her mask on in the building. She left, then sent her naive followers to call and harass this establishment and sought to ruin their reputation. A simple Google search of Tracey Barbie will reveal quite a bit about her character. She has a nasty reputation of posting people's private information (usually the cell numbers of her dates who don't want to continue with a second date) and slandering businesses when she is required to follow the rules of the business.  The recent one star reviews are from people who watch her livestream and blindly follow her. Tracey Barbie told her followers to call and harass Tommy Joe's because they yelled at her and kicked her out. Which was false.  Apparently, she believes she is invincible and the law will never catch up to her.  As for the business, it is always good to find businesses who work to protect their patrons and provide good service. Keep up the good work!

It's a shame when a business is bullied for protecting its clientele from COVID. I eat here often. I have seen this obnoxious patron Tracey repeatedly asked to put her mask on when walking through the restaurant. Today, we heard her telling her livestream audience (yes, she was secretly livestreaming) to leave bad reviews for this restaurant, just because they told her to WEAR A MASK AND FOLLOW THE RULES. Oh, horror!  Well, here are the vindictive reviews that have nothing to do with the food or service. I can say I love Tommy Joe's, it's staff (especially bartender, Juan), and appreciate not having to dodge a mask-less, unkempt, loud, drunken patron weaving her way to the bathroom. If you do come for a meal, their Chicken Buffalo Wrap is bomb, and we usually get the Crab Bites. Great margaritas when the roof is open. I highly recommend coming some lazy weekend afternoon and enjoying.
